# Get an unordered collection of unique city regions
# Data pruning, get those non-empty data
cities = set(City_time_series[
    ~City_time_series['ZHVI_AllHomes'].isnull() &
    # ZHVI--A smoothed seasonally adjusted measure of the median estimated home value across city
    ~City_time_series['Sale_Prices'].isnull()
                      ]['RegionName'].values)

City_time_series_year = City_time_series[City_time_series['RegionName'].isin(cities)].copy()
# Get 5 most expensive cities
highest_cost_cities = City_time_series_year[['RegionName', 'ZHVI_AllHomes']].groupby('RegionName').max().\
                      sort_values(by=['ZHVI_AllHomes'], ascending=False)[:5].index.values.tolist()
City_time_series_year = City_time_series_year[City_time_series_year.RegionName.isin(highest_cost_cities)]
City_time_series_year.year = City_time_series_year.Date.dt.year

In [265]:
# Adjust parameters to get lower mape(above model with default c=0.05，cr=0.8)
changepoint_prior_scale = [0.05, 0.06, 0.07, 0.08]
changepoint_range = [0.88, 0.89, 0.9, 0.91]
results = []

for idx, c in enumerate(changepoint_prior_scale):
    results.append([])
    for cr in changepoint_range:
        LA_m = Prophet(changepoint_prior_scale=c, changepoint_range=cr)
        LA_m.fit(LA_train);
        LA_future = LA_m.make_future_dataframe(periods=t, freq='M')
        LA_forecast = LA_m.predict(LA_future)
        LA_forecast['yhat_int32'] = np.int32(LA_forecast['yhat'])

        y_actual = LA_test.y.values
        y_forecasted = LA_forecast.iloc[-t:,2].values
        # Compute Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE)
        numerator = np.abs(y_actual - y_forecasted)
        diff = numerator / np.abs(y_actual)
        LA_mape = np.mean(diff) * 100
        results[idx].append(LA_mape)
        
        print('changepoint_prior_scale={}'.format(c))
        print('changepoint_range={}'.format(cr))
        print('Los Altos MAPE={}'.format(LA_mape))
